# SPEC.md sync

When a requested change alters behavior, defaults, APIs, config policy, or other
details documented in `SPEC.md`:

1. **Ask first** before editing `SPEC.md` (e.g. “This changes the Auto policy
   numbers in SPEC — update SPEC.md too?”).
2. Only update `SPEC.md` after the user confirms.
3. When updating, change the corresponding sections only (thresholds, timeouts,
   algorithms, UI behavior, checklist/defaults) so the spec matches the code.

Do not silently skip SPEC updates when the user has approved them, and do not
edit SPEC for pure refactors or internal cleanups that leave the documented
contract unchanged.
